  "final_text": "Multiple probes are attached \u2014 I need to pin the right one.\nReading the frame-event producer path and the inference consumer path to confirm where maintenance is (or isn't):\nFound it. Here's the full diagnosis:\n\n## Root cause: stale-read race on `nn_output_buffers` (NPU-DMA \u2192 CPU)\n\n**Live state** (CubeProgrammer hot-plug, since the gdb attach path hit the known N6 running-attach hang): the chip is parked in boot ROM (BOOT switch in DEV \u21d2 no flash boot), so the failing state wasn't live \u2014 but the source evidence is conclusive:\n\n1. **D-cache is enabled** (`main.c:73 SCB_EnableDCache()`), the **MPU is never configured** in app code (and was confirmed disabled on-target), so all DMA buffers sit in default-map **cacheable** Normal memory.\n\n2. **The only invalidate of the NPU output buffer happens *before* the hardware writes it** \u2014 `app.c:874`:\n   ```c\n   /* Invalidate output buffer before Hw access it */\n   CACHE_OP(SCB_InvalidateDCache_by_Addr(output_buffer, LL_ATON_NETWORK_OUT_1_SIZE_BYTES));\n   ```\n\n3. **The consumer CPU-reads it with no invalidate after the DMA write** \u2014 `app.c:1069\u20131075`, the postprocess task does `bqueue_get_ready(&nn_output_queue)` then `app_postprocess_run()` directly on the buffer.\n\nThe pre-invalidate-only pattern is racy on the M55: between the invalidate (NN thread) and the CPU read (postprocess thread), the core is free to **speculatively refill** lines of that cacheable buffer \u2014 no explicit access required. When that happens, postprocess reads the speculatively-cached (pre-inference) bytes instead of fresh NPU output. Classic intermittent \"DMA buffer reads stale data.\"\n\n(The capture path is clean: `nn_input_buffers` is camera-DMA-written and NPU-read \u2014 hardware on both sides, the `app.c:868` comment is correct. `lcd_*` buffers get explicit clean/clean-invalidate.)\n\n## Fix\n\nAdd the invalidate on the **consumer side, after the DMA write completes** \u2014 in `app.c` right after line 1069:\n\n```c\noutput_buffer = bqueue_get_ready(&nn_output_queue);\nassert(output_buffer);\nCACHE_OP(SCB_InvalidateDCache_by_Addr(output_buffer, NN_BUFFER_OUT_SIZE_ALIGN));\n```\n\nThe buffer is `ALIGN_32` with size rounded to `NN_BUFFER_OUT_SIZE_ALIGN`, so the by-addr invalidate won't clobber neighbours. Keep the line-874 pre-invalidate (it prevents dirty-line eviction corrupting the NPU's write). The bulletproof alternative is an MPU region marking the DMA buffers non-cacheable, but the one-line invalidate is the idiomatic fix here.\n\nTo verify on hardware afterwards: flip BOOT back to flash-boot, let the app run, and I can break at `app.c:1069` via a `DebugSession` and diff the CPU-visible buffer against a probe-side memory read \u2014 though note the N6 attach is currently flaky on this bench (DBG-012), so the simplest validation is just rebuilding and watching the pose output stop glitching."
}